news.title: Chandigarh administration remains adamant on property tax hike
news.para: With the new financial year underway, all financial works, reports, and related exercises have commenced in the municipal corporation (MC) according to the established process and procedure, without reconsidering the increased property tax, and making this segment of tax a major source of its own income.

news.title: Five FIRs filed against Ansal API in land scam case in Lucknow
news.para: In these FIRs, the victims alleged a fraud valuing more than Rs 50 lakh in the name of providing them plots, flats and shops. The police said further legal action would be taken based on cross-verification of allegations and evidence against the accused.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Only 2,760 of the 17,875 applications eligible for houses under PMAY
news.para: The District Urban Development Agency (DUDA), the nodal agency for distributing grants for constructing dwelling units under the scheme, had identified irregularities in grants last year and launched an investigation.

news.title: Gujarat RERA action against builder for pre-bookings
news.para: According to sources, GujRERA received a complaint from the buyer that the builder had taken Rs 1 lakh as token from him even before getting RERA registration for his project in Gandhinagar district.

news.title: Builder moves Telangana RERA over structural changes by flat owners
news.para: The builder sought interim relief, citing concerns that unauthorised modifications by the residents could affect the structural integrity of the building.

news.title: Noida: District magistrate directs officials to expedite polls' process in societies
news.para: Emphasising the need for timely elections, the DM directed all concerned officials to expedite the process. Elections have been delayed or never been held in at least 30 societies in GB Nagar.

news.title: China: Country Garden secures key bondholder group support for offshore debt overhaul
news.para: The company defaulted on its offshore debt in late 2023 and is now in a restructuring process that aims to cut $14.1 billion of that debt by 78%.

news.title: Gurugram Global City project to create five lakh job opportunities: Haryana CM
news.para: Saini said that the project, with an investment of over Rs 1 lakh crore, is expected to benefit approximately 16 lakh people. Once completed, it will generate around five lakh employment opportunities.

news.title: PWD issues order to make essential buildings in Delhi earthquake resistant
news.para: The meeting of the authority was held last month during which Delhi Chief Minister Rekha Gupta reviewed the city's earthquake preparedness.

news.title: RWA of Signature View Apartments in Delhi urges DDA for promised rent payments
news.para: The DDA had earlier classified the 336-flat Signature View Apartments in north Delhi's Mukherjee Nagar as a "dangerous building" and issued an e-tender for its demolition, citing structural safety concerns.

news.title: Karnataka government plans to recruit ADLRs to resolve land survey issues
news.para: He urged officials to complete pending survey work within two years and achieve Podi-mukta villages, noting that unresolved land survey issues often lead to disputes and violence.

news.title: Maradu civic body to provide land deeds to extremely poor families
news.para: The municipality officials said that those who receive the land will be co-opted into the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (PMAY) and the local body will provide assistance for the construction of houses there.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government allows new UDAs to clear building plans independently
news.para: The minus growth rate in registration revenues seems to have prompted the govt to walk the extra mile to give several concessions to builders and developers and pump energy into the real-estate sector over the last few months.

news.title: Nagpur sees 94% rise in built-up area since 1985
news.para: The built-up area stood at 73.76 sq km in 1985, accounting for 34.95% of the city's 211 sq km municipal area. Over 34 years, it grew by 69.34 sq km to reach 143.1 sq km by 2019.

news.title: Prayagraj civic body expands house tax collection to over 1.5 lakh more buildings
news.para: This taxation model is not limited to Prayagraj. Similar systems are set to be implemented in Gorakhpur and Varanasi, beginning this financial year.

news.title: Equity investment in Indian real estate rises 74% in Q4 FY25:  CBRE
news.para: Anshuman Magazine, Chairman & CEO - India, South-East Asia, Middle East & Africa, CBRE, said, "India's real estate sector continues to demonstrate resilience and attract sustained investor interest despite global headwinds."

news.title: Ajmera Realty's reports pre-sales of ₹1,080 crore in FY25
news.para: Ajmera Realty's collections stood at ₹646 crore in FY25, registering a growth of 13 per cent year-on-year.

news.title: NBCC auctions Amrapali flats worth Rs 7,000 crore to three developers
news.para: After the Uttar Pradesh government allowed NBCC to develop additional flats in the project, it estimated to generate an additional Rs 14,000 crore, which would have helped timely completion of stuck projects.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC to work with SRA, builders to redevelop Worli slums
news.para: The plan, arguably the first of its kind, envisages 12 acres of prime Govt and BMC land on the Worli sea face abutting the Coastal Road to be handed over to a consortium of city-based builders.

news.title: Telangana government launches slot booking system for property registrations
news.para: Revenue and registration minister Ponguleti Srinivas Reddy said slot booking started on a pilot basis at 22 sub-registrar offices, and the system would be extended to the entire state based on the outcome of the result.
